  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/15cook,Elder Quentin L. Cook,43,"In 1851, there were 52,165 total members of the Church. According to Church records and the “Religious Census of 1851” in England and Wales, there were over 28,000 members in those locations (see Robert L. Lively Jr., “Some Sociological Reflections on the Nineteenth-Century British Mission,” inMormons in Early Victorian Britain, ed. Richard L. Jensen and Malcolm R. Thorp [1989], 19–20)."
