  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,55,"King Benjamin described sincere repentance: “And again, believe that ye must repent of your sins and forsake them, and humble yourselves before God; and ask in sincerity of heart that he would forgive you; and now, if you believe all these things see that ye do them” (Mosiah 4:10)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,56,"See Russell M. Nelson, “The Power of Spiritual Momentum,”Liahona, May 2022, 98–99: “Start today to experience the joy of putting off the natural man. The Savior loves us always butespeciallywhen we repent. … Experience the joy and relief of repenting.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,57,"SeeAlma 5:14–15."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,58,"Dallin H. Oaks, “Our Message for Missionaries” (worldwide missionary broadcast, Jan. 20, 2016); see also Dallin H. Oaks, “Sin and Suffering,”Ensign, July 1992, 73."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,59,"3 Nephi 11:39; emphasis added."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,60,"2 Nephi 2:2."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/27schmutz,Elder Evan A. Schmutz,61,"SeeHebrews 5:8–9."
