  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,4,"Several years ago, Sister Nattress and I moved to Idaho, where we opened a new business. There were long days and nights at the office. Thankfully, we lived just a few blocks away from work. Each week, Shawna and our three daughters—all under the age of six—would come to the office to share lunch together."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,5,"On one such day after our family lunch, I noticed that our five-year-old daughter, Michelle, had left me a personal message, written on a Post-it Note and attached to my office telephone."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,6,"It simply read, “Dad, remember to love me. Love, Michelle.” This was a powerful reminder to a young father about those things that matter most."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,7,"Brothers and sisters, I testify thatour Heavenly Father always remembers usand that He loves us perfectly. My question is this: Do we remember Him? And do we love Him?"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,8,"Years ago, I served as a local Church leader. One of our young men, Danny, was outstanding in every way. He was obedient, kind, good, and had a great heart. However, when he graduated from high school, he started to associate with a rough crowd. He got involved in drugs, specifically methamphetamine, and traveled down the slippery slope of addiction and destruction. Before long, his appearance completely changed. He was hardly recognizable. The most significant change was in his eyes—the light in his eyes had dimmed. Several times I reached out to him, but to no avail. He wasn’t interested."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,9,It was difficult to see this incredible young man suffer and live a life that was not him! He was capable of so much more.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,10,"Then one day, his miracle began."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,11,"He attended a sacrament meeting where his younger brother shared his testimony prior to departing for a mission. During the meeting, Danny felt something he had not felt for a long time. He felt the love of the Lord. He finally had hope."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,12,"Although he had a desire to change, it was difficult for Danny. His addictions and the accompanying guilt were almost more than he could bear."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,13,"One particular afternoon, when I was out mowing our lawn, Danny pulled up in his car unannounced. He was struggling terribly. I turned off the mower, and we sat down together in the shade of the front porch. It was then that he shared the feelings of his heart. He truly wanted to come back. However, turning away from his addictions and lifestyle was extremely difficult. Adding to this, he felt so guilty, so ashamed for falling so far. He asked, “Can I really be forgiven? Is there really a way back?”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,14,"After he poured out his heart with these concerns, we readAlma chapter 36together:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,15,"“Yea, I did remember all my sins and iniquities. …"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,16,"“Yea, … the very thought of coming into the presence of my God did rack my soul with inexpressible horror” (verses 13–14)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,17,"After those verses, Danny said, “This is exactly how I feel!”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,18,"We continued:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,19,"“While I was harrowed up by the memory of my many sins, behold, I remembered also to have heard my father prophesy unto the people concerning the coming of one Jesus Christ, a Son of God, to atone for the sins of the world. …"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,20,"“And oh, what joy, and what marvelous light I did behold” (verses 17, 20)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,21,"As we read these passages, tears began to flow. Alma’s joy was the joy he had been searching for!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,22,"We discussed that Alma had been exceptionally wicked. However, once he repented, he never looked back. He became a devoted disciple of Jesus Christ. He became a prophet! Danny’s eyes widened. “A prophet?” he said."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,23,"I simply responded, “Yes, a prophet. No pressure on you!”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,24,"We discussed that while his sins did not rise to the level of Alma’s, the same promise of complete and perfect forgiveness is made to everyone—in and through the infinite Atonement of Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,25,"Danny now understood. He knew what he needed to do: he needed to begin his journey by trusting in the Lord and forgiving himself!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,26,"Danny’s mighty change of heart was nothing short of a miracle. Over time, his countenance changed, and the brightness in his eyes returned. He became temple worthy! He was finally back!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,27,"After several months, I asked Danny if he would like to submit an application to serve a full-time mission. His response was one of shock and awe."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,28,"He said, “I would love to serve a mission, but you know where I havebeen and the things I have done! I thought I was disqualified.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,29,"I responded, “You may be right. However, there is nothing precluding us from making a request. If you are excused, at least you will know that you expressed a sincere desire to serve the Lord.” His eyes lit up. He was thrilled with this idea. To him this was a long shot, but it was a chance he was willing to take."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,30,"A few weeks later, and to his amazement, another miracle occurred. Danny received a call to serve a full-time mission."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,31,"A few months after Danny arrived in the mission field, I received a telephone call. His president simply said, “What is it with this young man? He is the most incredible missionary I have ever seen!” You see, this president had received a modern-day Alma the Younger."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,32,"Two years later, Danny returned home with honor, having served the Lord with all his heart, might, mind, and strength."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,33,"Following his missionary report in sacrament meeting, I returned home, only to hear a knock at the front door. There stood Danny with tears welling in his eyes. He said, “Can we talk for a minute?” We went outside to the same porch step."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,34,"He said, “President, do you think I have truly been forgiven?”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,35,Now my tears accompanied his. Before me stood a devoted disciple of Jesus Christ who had given his all to teaching and testifying about the Savior. He was the embodiment of the healing and strengthening power of the Savior’s Atonement.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,36,"I said, “Danny! Have you looked in the mirror? Have you seen your eyes? They are filled with light, and you are beaming with the Spirit of the Lord. Of course you have been forgiven! You are amazing! Now what you need to do is move forward with your life. Don’t look back! Look forward with faith to the next ordinance.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,37,"Danny’s miracle continues today. He married in the temple and returned to school, where he received a master’s degree. He continues to serve the Lord with honor and dignity in his callings. More important, he has become an incredible husband and a faithful father. He is a devoted disciple of Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,38,"President Russell M. Nelson taught, “Without the [Savior’s] infinite Atonement, all mankind would be irretrievably lost.”Danny wasn’t lost, and neither are we to the Lord. He stands at the door to lift us, to strengthen us, and to forgive us. He always remembers to love us!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,39,"An incredible demonstration of the Savior’s love for God’s children is recorded in the Book of Mormon: “When Jesus had thus spoken, he cast his eyes round about again on the multitude, and beheld they were in tears, and did look steadfastly uponhim as if they would ask him to tarry a little longer with them” (3 Nephi 17:5)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,40,The Savior had already spent a full day ministering to the people. Yet He had more to do—He was to visit His other sheep; He was to go to His Father.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,41,"Notwithstanding these obligations, He discerned that the people desired for Him to tarry a little longer. Then, with the Savior’s heart full of compassion, one of the greatest miracles in the history of the world occurred:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,42,He stayed.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,43,He blessed them.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,44,He ministered to their children one by one.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,45,He prayed for them; He wept with them.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,46,And He healed them. (See3 Nephi 17.)
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,47,"His promise is eternal: He will heal us."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,48,"To those who have strayed from the covenant path, please know there is always hope, there is always healing, and there is always a way back."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,49,"His eternal message of hope is the healing balm for all who live in a troubled world. The Savior said, “I am the way, the truth, and the life” (John 14:6)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,50,"Brothers and sisters, let us remember to seek Him, to love Him, and to always remember Him."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,51,"I testify that God lives and that He loves us. I further testify that Jesus Christ is the Savior and Redeemer of the world. He is the mighty healer. I know that my Redeemer lives! In the name of Jesus Christ, amen."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,52,Note
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/33nattress,Elder K. Brett Nattress,53,"Russell M. Nelson, “Prepare for Blessings of the Temple,”Ensign, Mar. 2002, 21."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,4,"The Lord Jesus Christ said:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,5,"“I am the good shepherd: the good shepherd giveth his life for the sheep. …"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,6,"“As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father: and I lay down my life for the sheep.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,7,"In the Greek version of this scripture, the word forgoodalso means “beautiful, magnificent.” So today, I wish to speak of the Good Shepherd, the Beautiful Shepherd, the Magnificent Shepherd, even Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,8,"In the New Testament, He is called the “great shepherd,”the “chief Shepherd,”and “the Shepherd and Bishop of [our] souls.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,9,"In the Old Testament, Isaiah wrote that “he shall feed his flock like a shepherd.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,10,"In the Book of Mormon, He is called “the good shepherd”and the “great and true shepherd.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,11,"In the Doctrine and Covenants, He declares, “Wherefore, I am in your midst, and I am the good shepherd.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,12,"In our day, President Russell M. Nelson has declared: “The Good Shepherd lovingly cares for all sheep of His fold, and we are His true undershepherds. Our privilege is to bear His love and to add our own love to friends and neighbors—feeding, tending, and nurturing them—as the Savior would have us do.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,13,"More recently, President Nelson has said: “A hallmark of the Lord’s true and living Church will always be an organized, directed effort to minister to individual children of God and their families. Because it is His Church, we as His servants will minister to the one, just as He did. We will minister in His name, with His power and authority, and with His loving-kindness.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,14,"When the Pharisees and scribes murmured against the Lord, “saying, This man receiveth sinners, and eateth with them,”He responded by presenting three beautiful stories that we have come to know as the parable of the lost sheep, the parable of the lost coin, and the parable of the prodigal son."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,15,"It is interesting to note that when Luke, the Gospel writer, is introducing the three stories, he uses the wordparablein the singular, not in the plural.It appears that the Lord is teaching one unique lesson with three stories—stories that present different numbers: 100 sheep, 10 coins, and 2 sons."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,16,"The key number in each of these stories, however, is the numberone. And a lesson we might take from that number is that you might be an undershepherd for 100 elders and prospective elders in your elders quorum or an adviser to 10 young women or a teacher to 2 Primary children, but you always, always minister to them, care for them, and love them one by one, individually. You never say, “What a foolish sheep” or “After all, I do not really need that coin” or “What a rebellious son he is.” If you and I have with us “the pure love of Christ,”we, as the man in the story of the lost sheep, will “leave the ninety and nine … and go after that which is lost, until [… until … until we] find it.”Or, as the woman in the story of the lost coin, we will “light a candle, and sweep the house, and seek diligently [… diligently] till [… till … till we] find it.”If we have with us “the pure love of Christ,” we will follow the example of the father in the story of the prodigal son, who, when the son “was yet a great way off, … saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,17,Can we feel the urgency in theheart of the man who lost only one sheep? Or the urgency in the heart of the woman who lost just one coin? Or the ineffable love and compassion in the heart of the prodigal’s father?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,18,"My wife, Maria Isabel, and I served in Central America, being stationed in Guatemala City. There I had the opportunity to meet Julia, a faithful member of the Church. I had the impression to ask her about her family. Her mother died of cancer in 2011. Her father had been a faithful leader in his stake, serving as a bishop and as a counselor to his stake president for several years. He was a true undershepherd of the Lord. Julia told me of his tireless efforts to visit, to minister, and to serve. He indeed rejoiced in feeding and tending the precious sheep of the Lord. He remarried and stayed active in the Church."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,19,"A few years later, he went through a divorce, and now he had to attend church alone once again. He felt out of place and also felt that some people were critical of him because of his divorce. He stopped attending church as a negative spirit filled his heart."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,20,"Julia spoke highly of this wonderful undershepherd, who was a hardworking, loving, and compassionate man. I vividly remember that a feeling of urgency came to me as she was describing him. I just wanted to do something for that man, a man who had done so much for so many throughout those years."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,21,"She gave me his cell phone number, and I began calling him, hoping to have the chance to meet with him personally. After several weeks and many, many phone calls without success, one day he finally answered the phone."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,22,"I told him that I had met Julia, his daughter, and that I was captivated by the way he had served, ministered, and loved the precious sheep of the Lord for so many years. He was not expecting a comment like that. I told him that I really wanted to visit with him eye to eye, face to face. He asked me my purpose in proposing such a meeting. I replied, “I really want to meet the father of such a wonderful lady.” Then for a few seconds there was silence over the phone—a few seconds that seemed to me like an eternity. He simply said, “When and where?”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,23,"The day I met him, I invited him to share with me some of his experiences visiting, ministering, and serving the precious sheep of the Lord. As he was recounting some touching stories, I noticed that the tone of his voice changed and the same spirit he had felt so many times as an undershepherd came back. Now his eyes were filled with tears. I knew this was the right moment for me, but I found that I did not know what to say. I prayed in my mind, “Father, help me.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,24,"Suddenly, I heard myself saying, “Brother Florian, as a servant of the Lord, I apologize for our not being there for you. Please, forgive us. Give us another chance to show you that we do love you. That we need you. That you are important to us.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/34uceda,Elder Juan A. Uceda,25,"The following Sunday he was back. He had a long conversation with his bishop and remained active. A few months later he passed away—but he had come back. He had come back. I testify that with our Savior’s help, we can love His precious sheep and minister to them as He would. And so, there in Guatemala City the Lord Jesus Christ brought back one more precious sheep into His fold. And He taught me a lesson on ministering that I cannot forget. In the name of the Good Shepherd, the Beautiful Shepherd, the Magnificent Shepherd, even the Lord Jesus Christ, amen."
