  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,4,"With faith in Jesus Christ and hope in what they had heard of His miracles, the caregivers of a man with palsy brought him to Jesus. They were innovative in getting him there—uncovering the roof and lowering the man, on his bed, to the place where Jesus was teaching. When Jesus “saw their faith, he said [to the man with palsy], thy sins are forgiven thee.”And then, “Arise, and take up thy bed, and go thy way into thine house.”And immediately the man with palsy arose and took his bed and departed for home, “glorifying God.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,5,"What more do we know of the friends who provided care for the man with palsy? We know that the Savior recognizedtheirfaith. And having seen and heard the Savior and being a witness to His miracles, they were “amazed” and “glorified God.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,6,"Jesus Christ had provided the hoped-for healing—physicalrelieffrom pain and the crippling consequences of chronic disease. Significantly, the Savior also provided spiritualreliefin cleansing the man from sin."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,7,"And the friends—in their efforts to care for one in need, they found the source of relief; they found Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,8,"I testify that Jesus Christisrelief. Through the Atonement of Jesus Christ, we may be relieved of the burden and consequences of sin and be succored in our infirmities."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,9,"And because we love God and have covenanted to serve Him, we can partner with the Savior to help provide temporal and spiritual relief for those in need—and in the process find our own relief in Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,10,"Our beloved prophet, President Russell M. Nelson, invited us to overcome the world and find rest.He defined “true rest” as “relief and peace.” President Nelson said, “Because the Savior, through His infinite Atonement, redeemed each of us from weakness, mistakes, and sin, and because He experienced every pain, worry, and burden you have ever had, then as you truly repent and seek His help, you can rise above this present precarious world.”That is the relief Jesus Christ offers us!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,11,"Each of us is carrying a metaphorical backpack. It may be a basket balanced on your head or a satchel or a bundle of things wrapped in cloth and thrown over your shoulder. But for our thinking, let’s call it a backpack."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,12,"This metaphorical backpack is where we carry the burdens of living in a fallen world. Our burdens are like rocks in the backpack. Generally, there are three kinds:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,13,Rocks there of our own doing because of sin.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,14,"Rocks in our backpack because of the poor decisions, misconduct, and unkindness of others."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,15,"And rocks we carry because we are living in a fallen condition. These include the rocks of disease, pain, chronic illness, grief, disappointment, loneliness, and the effects of natural disasters."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,16,"I joyfully declare that our mortal burdens, these rocks in our figurative backpack, need not feel heavy."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,17,Jesus Christ can lighten our load.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,18,Jesus Christ can lift our burdens.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,19,Jesus Christ provides a way for us to be relieved of the weight of sin.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,20,Jesus Christ is our relief.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,21,"He said:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,22,"“Come unto me, all ye that labour and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest [that is, relief and peace]."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,23,"“Take my yoke upon you, and learn of me; for I am meek and lowly in heart: and ye shall find rest unto your souls."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,24,"“For my yoke is easy, and my burden is light.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,25,"That the yoke is easy and the burden is light presumes we get in the yoke with the Savior, that we share our burdens with Him, that we let Him lift our load. That means entering into a covenant relationship with God and keeping that covenant, which, as President Nelson has explained, “makeseverythingabout life easier.” He said, “Yoking yourself with the Savior means you have access toHisstrength and redeeming power.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,26,So why are we stingy with our rocks? Why would a weary baseball pitcher refuse to leave the mound when a reliever is there ready to complete the game? Why would I insist on maintaining my post alone when the Reliever stands ready to keep it with me?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,27,"President Nelson has taught, “Jesus Christ … stands with open arms, hoping and willing to heal, forgive, cleanse, strengthen, purify, and sanctify us.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,28,So why do we insist on carrying our rocks alone?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,29,It is intended as a personal question for each of you to consider.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,30,"For me, it is the age-old vice of pride. “I’ve got this,” I say. “No worries; I’ll get it done.” It’s the great deceiver who wants me to hide from God, to turn away from Him, to go at it alone."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,31,"Brothers and sisters, I can’t go at it alone, and I don’t need to, and I won’t. Choosing to be bound to my Savior, Jesus Christ, through the covenants I have made with God, “I can do all things through Christ which strengtheneth me.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,32,Covenant keepers are blessed with the Savior’s relief.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,33,"Consider this example in the Book of Mormon: The people of Alma were persecuted with “tasks upon them, and … task-masters over them.”Forbidden to pray vocally, they “did pour out their hearts to [God]; and he did know the thoughts of their hearts.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,34,"And “the voice of the Lord came to them in their afflictions, saying: Lift up your heads and be of good comfort, for I know of thecovenantwhich ye have made unto me; and I willcovenantwith my people and deliver them out of bondage."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,35,"“And I will also ease the burdens which are put upon your shoulders, that even you cannot feel them upon your backs.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,36,"And their burdens “were made light,” and “the Lord did strengthen them that they could bear up their burdens with ease, and they did submit cheerfully and with patience to all the will of the Lord.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,37,"Those covenant keepers received relief in the form of comfort, increased patience and cheerfulness, an ease in their burdens so that they felt light, and ultimately deliverance."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,38,Now let’s return to our own metaphorical backpack.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,39,"Repentance, through the Atonement of Jesus Christ, is what relieves us of the weight of the rocks of sin. And by this exquisite gift, God’s mercy relieves us from the heavy and otherwise insurmountable demands of justice."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,40,"The Atonement of Jesus Christ also makes it possible for us to receive strength to forgive, which allows us to unload the weight we carry because of mistreatment by others."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,41,So how does the Savior relieve us of the burdens of living in a fallen world with mortal bodies subject to grief and pain?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,42,"Often, He performs that kind of relief through us! As covenant members of His Church, we promise “to mourn with those that mourn” and “comfort those that stand in need of comfort.”Because we are “come into the fold of God” and are “called his people,” we “are willing to bear one another’s burdens, that they may be light.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,43,"Our covenantal blessing is to partner with Jesus Christ in providing relief, both temporal and spiritual, to all of God’s children. We are a conduit through which He provides relief."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,44,"And so, like the friends of the man with palsy, we “succor the weak, lift up the hands which hang down, and strengthen the feeble knees.”We “bear … one another’s burdens, and so fulfil the law of Christ.”As we do, we come to know Him, become like Him, and find His relief."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,45,What is relief?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,46,"It is the removal or lightening of something painful, troubling, or burdensome, or the strength to endure it. It refers to a person who takes the place of another. It is the legal correction of a wrong.The Anglo-French word comes from Old French, the wordrelever, or “to raise up,” and from the Latinrelevare, or “raise again.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,47,"Brothers and sisters, Jesus Christ is relief. I testify that He did rise again on the third day and, having fulfilled the loving and infinite Atonement, stands with open arms, offering to us the opportunity to rise again, be saved,andbe exalted and become like Him. The relief He offers us is everlasting."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/42johnson,President Camille N. Johnson,48,"Like the women visited by the angel on that first Easter morning, I wish to “go quickly” and with “great joy” to bring the word that He is risen.In the name of our Savior, Jesus Christ, amen."
