  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,4,"The ancient prophet Enoch, described in the Old Testament, the Doctrine and Covenants, and the Pearl of Great Price,was instrumental in establishing the city of Zion."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,5,"The scriptural account of Enoch’s call to serve indicates that “he heard a voice from heaven, saying: Enoch, my son, prophesy unto this people, and say unto them—Repent, … for their hearts have waxed hard, and their ears are dull of hearing, and their eyes cannot see afar off.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,6,"“And when Enoch had heard these words, he bowed himself to the earth … and spake before the Lord, saying: Why is it that I have found favor in thy sight, and am but a lad, and all the people hate me; for I am slow of speech; wherefore am I thy servant?”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,7,"Please notice that at the time of Enoch’s call to serve, he became acutely aware of his personal inadequacies and limitations. And I suspect all of us at one time or another in our Church service have felt much like Enoch. But I believe the Lord’s response to Enoch’s pleading question is instructive and applies to each of us today."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,8,"“And the Lord said unto Enoch: Go forth and do as I have commanded thee, and no man shall pierce thee. Open thy mouth, and it shall be filled, and I will give thee utterance. …"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,9,"“Behold my Spirit is upon you, wherefore all thy words will I justify; and the mountains shall flee before you, and the rivers shall turn from their course; and thou shaltabide in me, and I in you; therefore walk with me.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,10,"Enoch ultimately became a mighty prophet and a tool in God’s hands to accomplish a great work, but he did not start his ministry that way! Rather, his capacity over time was magnified as he learned to abide in and walk with the Son of God."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,11,I earnestly pray for the help of the Holy Ghost as we consider together the counsel given to Enoch by the Lord and what it can mean for you and me today.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,12,The Lord Jesus Christ extends to each of us the invitation to abide in Him.But how do we actually learn and come to abide in Him?
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,13,"The wordabidedenotes remaining fixed or stable and enduring without yielding. Elder Jeffrey R. Holland explained that “abiding” as an action means “‘[to] stay—but [to] stayforever.’ That is the call of the gospel message to … everyone … in the world. Come, but come to remain. Come with conviction and endurance. Come permanently, for your sake and the sake of all the generations who must follow you.”Thus, we abide in Christ as we are firm and steadfast inour devotion to the Redeemer and His holy purposes, in times both good and bad."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,14,"We begin to abide in the Lord by exercising our moral agency to take upon ourselves His yokethrough the covenants and ordinances of the restored gospel. The covenant connection we have with our Heavenly Father and His resurrected and living Son is the supernal source of perspective, hope, power, peace, and enduring joy; it also is the rock-solid foundationupon which we should build our lives."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,15,"We abide in Him by striving continually to strengthen our individual covenant bond with the Father and the Son. For example, praying sincerely to the Eternal Father in the name of His Beloved Son deepens and fortifies our covenant connection with Them."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,16,"We abide in Him by truly feasting upon the words of Christ. The Savior’s doctrine draws us, as children of the covenant, closer to Himand will tell us all things what we should do."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,17,"We abide in Him by preparing earnestly to participate in the ordinance of the sacrament, reviewing and reflecting on our covenant promises, and repenting sincerely. Worthily partaking of the sacrament is a witness to God that we are willing to take upon ourselves the name of Jesus Christ and strive to “always remember him”after the brief period of time required to participate in that sacred ordinance."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,18,And we abide in Him by serving God as we serve His children and minister to our brothers and sisters.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,19,"The Savior said, “If ye keep my commandments, ye shall abide in my love; even as I have kept my Father’s commandments, and abide in his love.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,20,"I briefly have described several of the many ways we can abide in the Savior. And I now invite each of us as His disciples to ask, seek, knock, and learn for ourselves by the power of the Holy Ghost other meaningful ways we can make Christ the center of our lives in all that we do."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,21,"The Savior’s promise to His followers is twofold: if we abide in Him, He will abide in us. But is it indeed possible for Christ to abide in you and me—individually and personally? The answer to this question is a resounding yes!"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,22,"In the Book of Mormon, we learn about Alma’s teaching and testifying to the poor whose afflictions had compelled them to be humble. In his instruction, he compared the word to a seed that must be planted and nourished, and he described “the word” as the life, mission, and atoning sacrifice of Jesus Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,23,"Alma said, “Begin to believe in the Son of God, that he will come to redeem his people, and that he shall suffer and die to atone for their sins; and that he shall rise again from the dead, which shall bring to pass the resurrection, that all men shall stand before him, to be judged at the last and judgment day, according to their works.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,24,"Given this description of “the word” by Alma, please consider the inspiring connection he then identifies."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,25,"“And now … I desire that ye shallplant this word in your hearts, and as it beginneth to swell even so nourish it by your faith. And behold,it will become a tree, springing upin youunto everlasting life. And then may God grant unto you that your burdens may be light, through the joy of his Son. And even all this can ye do if ye will.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,26,"The seed we should strive to plant in our hearts is the word—even the life, mission, and doctrine of Jesus Christ. And as the word is nourished by faith, it can become a tree springing upin usunto everlasting life."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,27,What was the symbolism of the tree in Lehi’s vision? The tree can be considered as a representation of Jesus Christ.
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,28,"My beloved brothers and sisters, is the Word in us? Are the truths of the Savior’s gospel written in the fleshy tables of our hearts?Are we coming unto and gradually becoming more like Him? Is the tree of Christ growing in us? Are we striving to become “new [creatures]”in Him?"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,29,"Perhaps this miraculous potential inspired Alma to ask: “Have ye spiritually been born of God? Have ye received his image in your countenances? Have ye experienced this mighty change in your hearts?”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,30,"We should always remember the Lord’s instruction to Enoch: “Thoushalt abide in me,and I in you.”And I testify the Savior’s promise to abide in us is true and available to every covenant-keeping member of His restored Church."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,31,"The Apostle Paul admonished believers who had received the Lord: “So walk ye in him.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,32,"Walking in and with the Savior highlights two vital aspects of discipleship: (1) obeying God’s commandments, and (2) remembering and honoring the sacred covenants that connect us to the Father and the Son."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,33,"John declared:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,34,"“And hereby we do know that we know him, if we keep his commandments."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,35,"“He that saith, I know him, and keepeth not his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,36,"“But whoso keepeth his word,in himverily is the love of God perfected: hereby know we that we arein him."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,37,"“He that saith he abideth in him ought himself also soto walk, even as he walked.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,38,"Jesus beckons to each of us, “Come, follow me”and “walk with me.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,39,"I testify that as we press forward in faith and walk in the meekness of the Lord’s Spirit,we are blessed with power, guidance, protection, and peace."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,40,"Alma describes a loving entreaty from the Lord to all living souls:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,41,"“Behold, he sendeth an invitation untoall men, for the arms of mercy are extended towards them, and he saith: Repent, and I will receive you."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,42,"“… Come unto me and ye shall partake of the fruit of the tree of life; yea, ye shall eat and drink of the bread and the waters of life freely.”"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,43,"I emphasize the absolute comprehensiveness of the Savior’s plea. He yearns to bless with His grace and mercy every single person who now lives, who has ever lived, and who will yet live upon the earth."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,44,"Some Church members accept as true the doctrine, principles, and testimonies proclaimed repeatedly from this pulpit in the Conference Center and in local congregations around the world—and yet may struggle to believe these eternal truths apply specifically in their lives and to their circumstances. They believe sincerely and serve dutifully, but their covenant connection with the Father and His redeeming Son has not yet become a living and transforming reality in their lives."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,45,"I promise that by the power of the Holy Ghost, you can know and feel the gospel truths I have attempted to describe are for you—for you individually and personally."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,46,"I joyfully witness that Jesus Christ is our loving and living Savior and Redeemer. If we abide in Him, He will abide in us.And as we walk in and with Him, we will be blessed to bring forth much fruit. I so testify in the sacred name of the Lord Jesus Christ, amen."
