  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,65,"I explained this principle in a devotional in 2017:"
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,66,"“Alma … ‘began to preachthe word of Godunto the people, entering into their synagogues, and into their houses; yea, and even they did preachthe wordin their streets’ [Alma 32:1; emphasis added]. He also compared the word of God to a seed."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,67,"“‘Now, if ye give place, that a seed may be planted in your heart, behold, if it be a true seed, or a good seed, if ye do not cast it out by your unbelief, that ye will resist the Spirit of the Lord, behold, it will begin to swell within your breasts; and when you feel these swelling motions, ye will begin to say within yourselves—It must needs be that this is a good seed, or thatthe wordis good, for it beginneth to enlarge my soul; yea, it beginneth to enlighten my understanding, yea, it beginneth to be delicious to me’ [Alma 32:28; emphasis added]."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,68,"“Interestingly, a good seed becomes a tree as it is planted in the heart and begins to swell, sprout, and grow."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,69,"“‘And behold, asthe treebeginneth to grow, ye will say: Let us nourish it with great care, that it may get root, that it may grow up, andbring forth fruitunto us. And now behold, if ye nourish it with much care it will get root, and grow up, and bring forth fruit."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,70,"“‘But if ye neglect the tree, and take no thought for its nourishment, behold it will not get any root; and when the heat of the sun cometh and scorcheth it, because it hath no root it withers away, and ye pluck it up and cast it out."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,71,"“‘Now, this is not because the seed was not good, neither is it because the fruit thereof would not be desirable; but it is because your ground is barren, and ye will not nourish the tree, therefore ye cannot have the fruit thereof."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,72,"“‘And thus, if ye will notnourish the word, looking forward with an eye of faith to the fruit thereof, ye can never pluck of the fruit of the tree of life."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,73,"“‘But if ye willnourish the word, yea,nourish the treeas it beginneth to grow, by your faith with great diligence, and with patience, looking forward tothe fruit thereof, it shall take root; and behold it shall bea tree springing up unto everlasting life’ [Alma 32:37–41; emphasis added]."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,74,"“… The central feature in Lehi’s dream is the tree of life—a representation of ‘the love of God’ [1 Nephi 11:21–22]."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,75,"“‘For God so loved the world, that he gave his only begotten Son, that whosoever believeth in him should not perish, but have everlasting life’ [John 3:16]."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,76,"“The birth, life, and atoning sacrifice of the Lord Jesus Christ are the greatest manifestations of God’s love for His children. As Nephi testified, this love was ‘most desirable above all things’ and ‘most joyous to the soul’ [1 Nephi 11:22–23; see also1 Nephi 8:12, 15].Chapter 11 of 1 Nephipresents a detailed description of the tree of life as a symbol for the life, ministry, and sacrifice of the Savior—the ‘condescension of God’ [1 Nephi 11:16]. The tree can be considered as a representation of Christ."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,77,"“One way of thinking about the fruit on the tree is as a symbol for the blessings of the Savior’s Atonement. The fruit is described as ‘desirable to make one happy’ [1 Nephi 8:10] and produces great joy and the desire to share that joy with others."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,78,"“Significantly, the overarching theme of the Book of Mormon, inviting all to come unto Christ [seeMoroni 10:32], is paramount in Lehi’s vision [see1 Nephi 8:19]” (“The Power of His Word Which Is in Us” [address given at seminar for new mission leaders, June 27, 2017], 4–5)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,79,"See2 Corinthians 3:3."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,80,"2 Corinthians 5:17."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,81,"Alma’s analogy teaches us that the desire to believe plants the seed in our hearts, nourishing the seed by our faith sprouts the tree of life, and nourishing the tree produces fruit of the tree, which is “sweet above all that is sweet” (Alma 32:42) and is “the greatest of all the gifts of God” (1 Nephi 15:36)."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,82,"Alma 5:14."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,83,"Moses 6:34; emphasis added."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,84,"Colossians 2:6."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,85,"1 John 2:3–6; emphasis added."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,86,"Luke 18:22."
  2023,"04",/general-conference/2023/04/57bednar,Elder David A. Bednar,87,"Moses 6:34."
